Congo Republic to Spend $60 Million on 2015 African Games

-- B y   R o b e r t   M b a k o u
-- 
2011-12-12T14:46:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-12/congo-republic-to-spend-60-million-on-2015-african-games.html
Congo Republic will spend 30 billion
 CFA francs  ($60 million) to host the 2012 All-Africa Games, said
Leon Alfred Opimbat, sports and physical education minister.  The money will be invested in sports infrastructure and on
training athletes, Opimbat told reporters in Brazzaville, the
capital, today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Mbakou in Johannesburg at 
 rmbakouo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
